<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<p class="p">The data assimilation technique follows Bayes’ theorem [
 <xref rid="pone.0170052.ref033" ref-type="bibr" class="xref">33</xref>], where the posterior probability π of observing the parameters Θ given the data 
 <bold class="bold">
  <italic class="italic">y</italic>
 </bold> is proportional to the likelihood 
 <italic class="italic">L</italic> of the data given the parameters times the prior probability distribution of the parameters, 
 <disp-formula id="pone.0170052.e006" class="disp-formula">
  <alternatives class="alternatives">
   <graphic xlink:href="pone.0170052.e006.jpg" id="pone.0170052.e006g" mimetype="image" position="anchor" orientation="portrait" class="graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
   <math id="M6" class="math">
    <mrow class="mrow">
     <mi class="mi">π</mi>
     <mo class="mo">(</mo>
     <mo class="mo">Θ</mo>
     <mo class="mo">∣</mo>
     <mi mathvariant="bold-italic" class="mi">y</mi>
     <mo class="mo">)</mo>
     <mo class="mo">∝</mo>
     <mi class="mi">L</mi>
     <mo class="mo">(</mo>
     <mi mathvariant="bold-italic" class="mi">y</mi>
     <mo class="mo">∣</mo>
     <mo class="mo">Θ</mo>
     <mo class="mo">)</mo>
     <mo class="mo">×</mo>
     <mi class="mi">π</mi>
     <mo class="mo">(</mo>
     <mo class="mo">Θ</mo>
     <mo class="mo">)</mo>
     <mo class="mo">.</mo>
    </mrow>
   </math>
  </alternatives>
  <label class="label">(3)</label>
 </disp-formula>
</p>
